# Next.js and TypeScript

- Keep Server Components as the default. Add `'use client'` only for state, effects, browser APIs, or client-only UI libraries.
- Define props and shared data shapes with named `type` or `interface`; avoid `any`. Use `unknown` for external input and narrow it.
- Prefer immutable state updates with object/array copies. Never mutate React state directly.
- Keep components cohesive. Extract helpers or child components when a section becomes hard to scan.
- Validate user input at boundaries with schema-based validation when data leaves the browser or enters an API route.
- Handle async failures explicitly and show user-friendly messages in UI flows.
- Use `next/link` for internal navigation and normal anchors for `tel:`, `mailto:`, and external URLs.
- Keep shadcn/ui usage consistent: compose existing `components/ui` primitives before adding new UI dependencies.
- For images, prefer `next/image` when real assets are added; keep alt text meaningful for marketing and accessibility.
- Do not weaken `tsconfig` or `next.config` safety settings without calling out the trade-off.
